Note.EditorialCommentary: The Warsaw intabulator seems here to have misread a dotted Maxima as a dotted Longa, and the Tenor subsequently drops out for the next few measures, producing an uncharacteristically thin texture.

The Bassus is entirely conjectural here: the organ tablature seems to have moved the Altus down an octave in this passage, producing many structural 4ths and eliminating the original bass, which is any case quite restricted harmonically.
